"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-07-30-paris-2024-olympics-team-nigeria-captain-opeyori-ready-to-conquer-badminton-opponent\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  Nigeria's badminton star, Anuoluwapo Opeyori has declared his readiness to compete for honours at the 2024 Olympic Games in Paris.  Opeyori will begin his medal quest against Switzerland's Tobias Kuenzi at La Chapelle Arena on Tuesday (today).  The athlete took to social media to express his readiness for the clash with Kuenzi.  \\\"First matchday at the 2024 Paris Olympics tomorrow (Tuesday) by 6:30pm C.A.T. I am very sure you guys can tell how excited I am. I will give it nothing but my absolute best.  \\\"I am excited for my first game in the Olympics Paris 2024. It is an honour to represent Nigeria. I have put my heart and soul into training every day and night, and I am happy to represent,\\\" Opeyori wrote on X.  The 27-year-old will be making his second appearance at the Olympics following his debut four years ago in Tokyo.  Transfer: Atletico Madrid in talks to sign Chelsea midfielder for Diego Simeone  Mbappe buys football club  Paris 2024 Olympics: Nigeria's dismal performance worries enthusiasts  Paris 2024 Olympics: D'Tigress' Wakama wins Best Coach award  Paris 2024 Olympics: Brume vows to  bounce back from disappointing outing  Paris 2024 Olympics: Sports Minister apologises to Nigerians after disastrous outing  Paris 2024 Olympics: Team Nigeria officially finishes without single medal  Paris 2024 Olympics: Nigeria's last medal hope Reuben crashes out in Wrestling  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"